The Telegraph - Calcutta
 NCA meeting in city
New Delhi: The National Cricket Academy committee will meet in Calcutta on April 10 to approve the venues for zonal cricket academies for the current year. The meeting, to be chaired by NCA chief Sunil Gavaskar, will also select coaches, physios and trainers for the zonal academies and the NCA, academy vice-chairman C. K. Khanna said Friday. It will also select bowling, fielding and wicket-keeping coaches who will visit the zonal academies. The proposals of chief Talent Research Development Officer Dilip Vengsarkar will also be discussed. (PTI)  Copyright 
